sub_title: Management Consulting for Customer Experience & Operations Strategy. International Business Graduate with Cum Laude distinctions.
summary:
I am Italian and German and have lived in Los Angeles, Phoenix, Florence, Maastricht, Barcelona and am currently working in Milan, Italy. 

I graduated with Cum Laude distinctions from an International Business bachelor's degree with a  marketing specialization. I conducted my thesis on a small scale empirical research, diving into the effect of personalization in advertisements for Gen Z customerâ€™s buying intention across different product categories. The research yielded conclusions with significant results.

Looking ahead, I aim to expand my knowledge in management consulting, business development and data analytics. 

I am a pro-active team member who loves to take up a challenge, through analytical thinking, creativity, taking responsibility and continuously learning. 

I enjoy meeting new people, living new experiences, learning by doing, travelling and engaging in a range of sports from skiing to ball games to skating.

Speaking English and Italian fluently, having an advanced level of Spanish and intermediate proficiency of German and growing up in a dynamic environment, has taught me to appreciate international communities and experiences.

If I had to describe myself with one word it would be Energetic.

My favourite quote is from Napoleon Hill: "You are the Master of Your Own Destiny."
